Oil included. Robinair, a Bosch Automotive Service Solutions brand, is a global leader in service tools and equipment based in Owatonna, Minnesota. Robinair is recognized throughout the world as the quality and performance leader in AC/R evacuation tools and this position has led to its success with the full range of products that serve the heating/ventilating/air conditioning/refrigeration (HVAC-R) and mobile markets, which includes the automotive aftermarket along with other industries such as agriculture and construction.']

['The Slip Yoke Eliminator Kit from Outland Automotive is a must for any 88-06 Jeep Wrangler YJ/TJ or 88-01 Cherokee XJ models with a 2-inch or larger suspension lift. When a vehicle is lifted, the geometry of the driveline is altered which will often result in driveline vibrations. Over time, these vibrations can lead to accelerated wear and premature failure of u-joints and bearings. The Slip Yoke Eliminator Kit incorporates a shorter and stronger transfer case main shaft with a fixed output yoke, doing away with the failure-prone slip yoke for more reliable off-road performance. The SYE Kit requires use of a CV-style drive shaft which improves driveline alignment over a broader range of suspension articulation and chassis movement. The SYE Kit will not work with cable driven speedometers and includes detailed installation instructions.']

ACT LE1-HDSS HD Pressure Plate with Performance Street Sprung Clutch Disc
["This ACT clutch kit includes a Heavy Duty pressure plate, Performance Street disc, release bearing, pilot bearing and alignment tool. The Heavy Duty pressure plate allows for a 20 to 50 percent increase in clamp load over the stock unit. ACT's Heavy Duty pressure plate features precision CNC machined parts, drive straps and rivets to securely locate contact face to the cover for quiet, trouble-free operation. The Heavy Duty pressure plate will have a stock to moderate pedal feel. ACT pressure plates feature creative diaphragm designs to increase clamp load, reduce deflection and maximize clutch life. All diaphragms endure an exclusive four-stage, heat-treating process for unparalleled performance. The Heavy Duty pressure plate meets SFI Specification 1.1. ACT Performance Street discs are modified with reduced marcel for faster shift action to complement ACT pressure plates. Performance Street discs have higher copper content friction lining for heat tolerance and steel-backed lining for greater burst strength and durability.
